<div class=WordSection1>

<h1 align=center style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;
text-align:center'><b><span style='font-size:24.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:
PMingLiU;mso-font-kerning:18.0pt;mso-fareast-language:ZH-TW'>Albert C. S. Chung
(D. Phil., <a href="http://www.oriel.ox.ac.uk/">Oriel College</a>, <a
href="http://www.ox.ac.uk/">University of Oxford</a>, U.K.)<o:p></o:p></span></b></h1>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto'><span
style='mso-fareast-language:ZH-TW'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto'><span
style='mso-fareast-language:ZH-TW'>Prof. Chung received his <span class=SpellE><span
class=GramE>B.Engg</span></span>. degree (First-Class <span class=SpellE>Honours</span>)
in Computer Engineering from the <a href="http://www.hku.hk">University of Hong
Kong</a> in 1995. He was an exchange student at the <a href="http://www.ubc.ca/">University
of British Columbia</a>, Canada, from 1992-93 with the Cathay Pacific Visiting
Student Award. He joined <a href="http://www.ust.hk/">The Hong Kong</a><a
href="http://www.ust.hk"> University of Science and Technology</a> </span><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:PMingLiU;mso-fareast-language:ZH-HK'>(HKUST) </span><span
style='mso-fareast-language:ZH-TW'>in 1996 and received his M.Phil. degree in
Computer Science in 1998. He then joined the <a
href="http://www.robots.ox.ac.uk/~mvl/">Medical Vision Laboratory</a>, <a
href="http://www.robots.ox.ac.uk/">Robotics Research Group</a> at the <a
href="http://www.ox.ac.uk/">University of Oxford</a>, U.K. as a doctoral
research student in 1998 and graduated in 2001</span><span style='mso-fareast-font-family:
PMingLiU;mso-fareast-language:ZH-HK'> with D.Phil. degree in Engineering
Science</span><span style='mso-fareast-language:ZH-TW'>. Prof. Chung was a <a
href="http://cf.spanner.org/scholars/albert-c-s-chung">Croucher scholar</a>
(1998 Â– 2001) with the <a href="http://www.croucher.org.hk/">Croucher
Foundation</a> Scholarship. He was a visiting scientist at the <a
href="http://www.ai.mit.edu">Artificial Intelligence Laboratory</a>, <a
href="http://www.mit.edu">Massachusetts Institute of Technology</a>, U.S.A.
(Sept 2001 Â– Feb 2002). </span><span style='mso-fareast-font-family:PMingLiU;
mso-fareast-language:ZH-HK'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto'><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:PMingLiU;mso-fareast-language:ZH-HK'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto'><span
style='mso-fareast-language:ZH-TW'>Prof.</span><span style='mso-fareast-font-family:
PMingLiU;mso-fareast-language:ZH-HK'> Chung</span><span style='mso-fareast-language:
ZH-TW'> </span><span style='mso-fareast-font-family:PMingLiU;mso-fareast-language:
ZH-HK'>was honored to receive </span><span style='color:black;mso-fareast-language:
ZH-TW'>the British Machine Vision Association <a
href="https://britishmachinevisionassociation.github.io/bursaries/sullivan-prize.html"><span
style='mso-field-code:" HYPERLINK \0022https\:\/\/britishmachinevisionassociation\.github\.io\/bursaries\/sullivan-prize\0022 "'><span
style='mso-field-code:" HYPERLINK \0022http\:\/\/www\.bmva\.org\/sullivan\0022 "'>Sullivan
Thesis Award</span></span></a> for the best doctoral thesis submitted to a U</span><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:PMingLiU;color:black;mso-fareast-language:ZH-TW'>nited
Kingdom</span><span style='color:black;mso-fareast-language:ZH-TW'> university
in the field of computer </span><span style='mso-fareast-font-family:PMingLiU;
color:black;mso-fareast-language:ZH-TW'>vision </span><span style='color:black;
mso-fareast-language:ZH-TW'>or natural vision</span><span style='mso-fareast-font-family:
PMingLiU;color:black;mso-fareast-language:ZH-HK'> in 2002; the </span><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:PMingLiU;color:black;mso-fareast-language:ZH-TW'>Best</span><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:PMingLiU;color:black;mso-fareast-language:ZH-HK'>
Ten Lecturers Award at HKUST in 2010</span><span style='color:black;mso-fareast-language:
ZH-TW'>; Best Teaching Award for MSc Program in Information Technology in 2018;
and Best Teaching Award for MSc Program in Big Data Technology in 2018. </span><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:PMingLiU;mso-fareast-language:ZH-HK'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto'><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";color:black;mso-fareast-language:
ZH-TW'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto'><span
style='mso-fareast-language:ZH-TW'>Prof.<span style='color:black'> Chung
founded the Lo Kwee-Seong Medical Image Analysis Laboratory in 2005 (2005 Â–
2021) with a generous donation from the K.S. Lo Foundation, Hong Kong. The
laboratory </span>focused on interdisciplinary research aiming at creating and
applying engineering techniques <span class=GramE>in the area of</span> medical
image analysis, with the ultimate goal of improving the quality of healthcare
in Hong Kong, China, and other regions. He is now </span><span
style='mso-fareast-language:ZH-HK'>the Director of The HKUST Research Center
for Medical Imaging and Analysis.</span><span style='mso-fareast-language:ZH-TW'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto'><span
style='mso-fareast-language:ZH-TW'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto'><span
style='mso-fareast-language:ZH-TW'>Prof.</span><span style='mso-fareast-language:
ZH-HK'> Chung was the director of the <a
href="http://www.cpeg.ust.hk/cgi-bin/eng/index.php">Computer Engineering
Undergraduate <span class=SpellE>Programme</span></a>, HKUST 2010-2012
(Associate director, 2008-2010). He was the UG Coordinator (2015 Â– 2016) and
Associate Head (2016 Â– 2019) at the <a href="https://www.cse.ust.hk/">Department
